def find_dup(arr):
    return max([i for i in arr if arr.count(i) > 1])

from collections import Counter
find_dup = lambda xs: Counter(xs).most_common(1)[0][0]
find_dup = lambda l: [v for i, v in enumerate(l) if l.index(v) != i][0]

def find_dup(arr):
